<SLUG> BC-BKN-SPURS-ROBINSON-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROBINSON HAS GOOD NUMBERS IN NO. 2 ROLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Being the San Antonio Spurs' undisputed go-to guy
and leader was something that no longer appealed to David Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   Especially after he saw the way Tim Duncan was terrorizing
opposing players.
</P>
<P>
   Thus, earlier this season Robinson decided it was time for
Duncan to be the Spurs' headline player, and he graciously stepped
into the background. That, coincidentally, was about the same time
the Spurs rebounded from a horrible 6-8 start to launch a drive
that finds them within two victories of the NBA championship.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just want to win, and I'll do anything that I can to help
this team win,'' Robinson said. ``Even if that means just
rebounding, blocking shots and playing defense.''
</P>
<P>
   But make no mistake about it. The Spurs need Robinson _ as much
as they need Duncan _ to put the finishing touches on what has
become the finest season in the team's history.
</P>
<P>
   That was more apparent last night at the Alamodome during Game 2
of the NBA Finals against the New York Knicks, which the Spurs won,
80-67. While Duncan was putting on his usual star-studded
performance, Robinson was once again steady as a rock, finishing
with 16 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks.
</P>
<P>
   The five blocks were significant, because Robinson really
disrupted any hopes the Knicks had of establishing an inside game.
He also altered many of their shots, and the hapless Knicks shot
just 32.9 percent from the field.
</P>
<P>
   Although Spurs fans often shower Duncan with chants of ``MVP,
MVP, MVP,'' Robinson said he has no problem with the adulation
directed at the second-year forward from Wake Forest.
</P>
<P>
   ``Man, Tim deserves all of the accolades that he gets, and
probably some more that he doesn't get,'' Robinson said. ``He is
such a great player.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've even learned a few things from here. I just hope he
continues progressing the way he has because, if he does, the sky's
the limit for him.''
</P>
<P>
   Robinson was one of the main reasons Spurs fans started chanting
``Sweep, sweep, sweep'' with less than three minutes left in the
game. The Spurs swept their two previous playoff series, against
Portland and the Los Angeles Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   Game 3 is scheduled Monday night at New York's Madison Square
Garden.
</P>
<P>
   Duncan, who collected 25 points and 15 rebounds last night, will
be the first to tell anyone within listening distance that he has
benefited handsomely from Robinson's presence.
</P>
<P>
   ``It has helped me tremendously, not only as a player on the
floor, but just as a person giving me advice on the league, on
situations, on everything else,'' Duncan said. ``He's been a great
person to be there for me. It's been a lot of fun being with him.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
