differently? According to the influential economist Deidre
McCloskey, formerly Donald McCloskey before her sex change, they
do. By Louis Uchitelle. (2000 words)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo is being sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   ARCHITECTURE-LAND (Undated) _ An architecture critic on the
too-often-ignored battles over space and land, where architecture
becomes a history of style written by the victors. By Herbert
Muschamp. (1600 words)
</P>
<P>
   STOLEN-BOOKS (Undated) _ There is already a best-seller list,
but what is on the best-stealer's list _ which books are most
frequently stolen? It turns out to be the Beat poets and the Bible.
By Joyce Jensen. (925 words)
</P>
<P>
   MOMA-MALEVICH (New York) _ The Museum of Modern Art settles with
heirs of the Russian artist Malevich over a cache of his paintings.
By Carol Vogel.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NYT News Service &LR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
