convivial place. From its roots in the late 1960's as the ARPAnet,
the Pentagon-funded experiment that connected computers at computer
research laboratories and universities, the Net was once an
intimate virtual coffeehouse where software and opinions were
freely shared. Locks and passwords were unknown in a hacker's
