<HEADLINE>
CONNECTICUT SENATOR MARRIES VICE CHAIRMAN OF EXPORT-IMPORT BANK  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Utah)   By MIKE ALLEN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HARTFORD, Conn. _ U.S. Sen. Christopher Dodd, a Connecticut
Democrat, was married Friday night at his home in East Haddam to
Jackie Marie Clegg, the vice chairman and chief operating officer
of the Export-Import Bank of the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Clegg and Dodd had dated for about 10 years, his office
said, and she accompanied him during his successful campaign last
fall for a fourth term. The engagement and wedding were a well-kept
secret and only a few relatives and friends attended the service,
held on a bank of the Connecticut River. The ceremony was performed
by Judge Robert N. Chatigny of U.S. District Court in Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
   An immediate honeymoon is not planned, and Dodd expects to be in
his Capitol Hill office on Monday, a spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
   Before joining the Export-Import Bank, Ms. Clegg was a
legislative assistant for 10 years to Sen. Jack Garn, a Republican
from Utah.
</P>
<P>
   She was born in Orem, Utah, and received a master's degree in
national securities studies from Georgetown University and an
undergraduate degree from Southern Utah University. She is the
daughter of Carl B. Clegg and the late Grace Meacham Clegg.
</P>
<P>
   Dodd, 55, the state's senior senator, was divorced after a brief
marriage early in his career. He was born in Willimantic, Conn. His
father, the late Thomas J. Dodd, also was a U.S. senator from
Connecticut.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
