<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-PROFILE _ AUSTIN _ Many Americans seem to like Texas
governor George Walker Bush very much and believe that the first
election of the 21st century is his to lose. However, they don't
seem to know him very well. After all, he has strenuously spent at
least the last year not running for president. Last weekend,
though, during a trip to Iowa and New Hampshire he finally declared
he's in the race. And now the nation will start getting to know who
this son of a former president really is. (Beach Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This package has moved. Package includes
BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE1, BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE2,
BUSH-PROFILE-COX-TAKE3, BUSH-TIMELINE-COX and photos. A shorter
version of the profile has also moved as BUSH-PROFILE-SHORT-COX.
The shorter version is available for sale as a full-page layout at
www.nytsyn.com/pageexpress.)
</P>
<P>
   GORE-ADVISERS _ WASHINGTON _ Who are the people who surround
Vice President Al Gore? What does it tell us about him?
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Friday, June 18 in the (w) Washington and (p)
politics categories. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
