MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ One day in August, 1997, 29-year-old
Carrie May didn't report to work at a local convenience store, and
instead locked herself in her Phoenix apartment, put a
newly-purchased pistol to her head and, speaking through the closed
front door, told her mother she was going to kill herself.
